{
  "texts": [
    "As pseudoobservable proxies for the relevant experimental measurements (ϵ K, ∆m B d,s,...), we use the bounds on the relevant low-energy WCs from [49], which we report in table 12.The expressions of these quantities in terms of SMEFT WCs are given in appendix A.7.• Semi-leptonic charged-current processes involving the transitions b → cℓν and b → uℓν.In this category we include the LFU ratios R D and R * D, defined asR D ( *) = B(B → D ( *) τ ν) B(B → D ( *) ℓν), (3.4)as well as the branching ratiosB(B c → τ ν) and B(B u → τ ν).",
    "(3.5)For R D ( *), we take the values provided by HFLAV both for the experimental average as well as for the SM predictions [46], and we collect the relevant expressions in terms of SMEFT WCs in appendix A.4.",
    "For the B u branching fraction, we useB (B u → τ ν) exp = 1.09(24) × 10 -4 [37] and B (B u → τ ν) SM = 0.812(54) × 10 -4 [38].For the B c case, only an upper bound is available.",
    "Following [50,51], we take it to be B (B c → τ ν) exp < 0.1 (95% CL).",
    "For the SM theory prediction we use B (B c → τ ν) SM = 0.023 [50]."
  ]
}